input_args.text: 'Snow reports from around the Northland through 3 p.m. Saturday By Andrew Krueger on Nov 19, 2016 at 3:15 p.m. Brian Parendo of Esko shovels heavy, wet show from his driveway Friday morning. "I\'m happy it lasted this long," he said, referring to the long spell of warm weather that preceded the storm. Bob King / rking@duluthnews.com Snow reports from around the Northland as of 3 p.m. Saturday, as relayed by the National Weather Service in Duluth. The greatest total was near Leader in Cass County; the total at the Duluth airport was corrected on Saturday from a higher total that had been reported Friday night. Recommended for you'
